"{\n  \"text\": \"Hey everybody, Scotty here at the Regenerative Agriculture Project in Neadville, Texas, and today we are putting the flat pile uh that we created last week onto the aerated static pipe. And you can see there's already a layer down. That's the plenum layer. That's a bunch of wood chips that helps the air flow through the compost as we put it on. And what we're doing here is we let it break down for about a week on the flat pile and then as we put it on this pile it gets mixed up a little bit better, but it's already a little broken down, so that helps in the uh mixing of it as we put on this pipe. We found that if we just did it directly, it didn't there's too many pockets of nitrogen, carbon, it didn't mix well. So we let it break down for a week on the flat pile and then we add it to the uh aerated stag pipe. And you can see we're putting the sprinkler system on there to get it good and wet as we're going. And in the foreground there is the old pile that was too carbonous, and there you can see we're gonna use it as a carbon cap. That means that we're putting it on top of the carbon or the aerated stag pile in order to capture the carbon but also prevent flies and smell.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Hey everybody, Scotty here at the Regenerative Agriculture Project in Neadville, Texas, and today we are putting the flat pile uh that we created last week onto the aerated static pipe.\",\n      \"start\": 0.16,\n      \"end\": 11.04,\n      \"duration\": 10.88,\n      \"confidence\": 0.989,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" He\",\n          \"start\": 0.16,\n          \"end\": 0.24,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 0.991\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"y\",\n          \"start\": 0.24,\n          \"end\": 0.32,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 0.999\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" ever\",\n          \"start\": 0.4,\n          \"end